The paper deals with the reachability problem in timed automata, which is a topic in formal methods and verification. The use of zone-based approaches and algorithms for efficient computation of zones is also a common theme in this area. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of abstraction techniques, which is a common theme in algorithm design and analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely category as well. The use of timed automata and related techniques for modeling and analysis of cyber-physical systems also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as possible categories.
